Posted: Wed Dec 29, 2010 2:07 pm
A double figure-eight is a much better knot than a bowline in a lot of scenarios. It is more time-consuming to tie (unless it's on a bight, in which case it is just as fast and easy) and it becomes difficult to untie after it has been heavily loaded, but it is much more secure than a bowline. It is also a stronger knot since the radius of the curves in the rope within the knot is larger. Climbers love making fun of boyscouts who insist that the bowline is the solution to everything.
